nazionale Milano<ref name=\"Guerin d'Oro\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/italpoy.html |title=Italy - Footballer of the Year |publisher=RSSSF |accessdate=6 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150121013030/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/italpoy.html |archivedate=21 January 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n*Pirata d'Oro (Internazionale Player Of The Year): 1995<ref>{{cite web|author=Inter.it staff, inter(a t)inter.it |url=http://inter.it/aas/news/reader?L=en&N=24665&stringa=%22player%20of%20the%20year%22 |title=F.C. Internazionale Milano |publisher=Inter.it |date=17 November 2006 |accessdate=14 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n* [[Guerin d'Oro]]: [[1996\u201397 Serie A|1996\u201397]]\n\n;[[Bologna F.C.]]<ref name=\"Guerin d'Oro\"/>\n* Guerin d'Oro: 2004\u201305\n\n===Orders===\n:[[File:Cavaliere OMRI BAR.svg|left|50px]] 5th Class/Knight: ''[[Italian orders of merit|Cavaliere Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana]]'': 1991<ref name=\"5th class\">{{cite web|url=http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/Onorificenze.aspx?pag=3045&qIdOnorificenza=&cognome=&nome=&daAnno=1800&aAnno=2014&luogoNascita=&testo=&ordinamento=2 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150320014016/http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/Onorificenze.aspx?pag=3045&qIdOnorificenza=&cognome=&nome=&daAnno=1800&aAnno=2014&luogoNascita=&testo=&ordinamento=2 |url-status=dead |archive-date=20 March 2015 |title=Onoreficenze |website=quirinale.it |language=Italian |date=30 September 1991 |accessdate=19 March 2015 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n* {{FIFA player|77257|Gianluca Pagliuca}}\n* {{NFT player|pid=10705}}\n\n{{Pirata d'Oro}}\n{{navboxes colour\n|title=Italy squads\n|bg= #0066bc\n|fg= #FFFFFF\n|list1=\n{{Italy football squad 1988 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Italy squad 1990 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Italy squad 1994 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Italy men's football squad 1996 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Italy squad 1998 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pagliuca, Gianluca}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy international footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:U.C. Sampdoria players]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:Bologna F.C. 1909 players]]\n[[Category:Ascoli Calcio 1898 F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Serie B players]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:1990 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:1994 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:1998 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Italy B international footballers]]\n[[Category:UEFA Cup winning players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}}\n{{Cleanup|date=October 2015|reason=Statistics about national and continental cups are missing}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Gianluca Pagliuca\n| fullname           = Gianluca Pagliuca\n| image              = Gianluca Pagliuca.jpg \n| caption            = Pagliuca with [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in 1989\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|12|18}}<ref name=yahoo/>\n| birth_place        = [[Bologna]], Italy<ref name=yahoo/>\n| height             = 1.90m<ref name=yahoo/>\n| position           = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1        = 1984\u20131986 |youthclubs1 = [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]\n| years1             = 1987\u20131994 |clubs1 = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]   |caps1 = 198 |goals1 = 0\n| years2             = 1994\u20131999 |clubs2 = [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]] |caps2 = 165 |goals2 = 0\n| years3             = 1999\u20132006 |clubs3 = [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]]  |caps3 = 248 |goals3 = 0\n| years4             = 2006\u20132007 |clubs4 = [[Ascoli Calcio 1898|Ascoli]]  |caps4 = 23  |goals4 = 0\n| totalcaps          = 634       |totalgoals = 0\n| nationalyears1     = 1989      |nationalteam1 = [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]]<ref name=figc/> |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2     = 1996      |nationalteam2 = Olympic Italy<ref name=figc/> | nationalcaps2 = 3 | nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3     = 1990\u20131998 |nationalteam3 = [[Italy national football team|Italy]] |nationalcaps3 = 39 |nationalgoals3 = 0\n| medaltemplates =\n{{MedalTeam|{{fb|ITA}}}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[1990 FIFA World Cup|Italy 1990]]|}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[1994 FIFA World Cup|USA 1994]]|}}\n}}\n'''Gianluca Pagliuca''' ({{IPA-it|d\u0292an\u02c8lu\u02d0ka pa\u028e\u02c8\u028eu\u02d0ka}}; born 18 December 1966) is an Italian [[Manager (association football)|football coach]] and former professional [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].\n\nHe is regarded by pundits as one of the greatest goalkeepers of his generation,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/2012/01/25/news/buffon_miglio_portiere_25_anni-28741113/|title=Buffon miglior portiere degli ultimi 25 anni|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|language=italian|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-gkoy98.html|title=IFFHS' World's Best Goalkeeper of the Year 1998|website=The Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/1998/luglio/05/cosa_resta_questa_Italia_ga_0_9807053256.shtml|title=Cosa resta di questa Italia|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|author=Lodovico Maradei|date=5 July 1998|accessdate=10 July 2016}}</ref> and one of Italy's best keepers ever.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-century.html#eukoy|title=IFFHS' Century Elections - Europe - Keeper of the Century|website=The Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation.|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10265~3816628,00.html|title=Inter Milan goalkeeping legend Pagliuca reveals Villa love|publisher=[[Aston Villa F.C.]]|author=Rob Bishop|accessdate=19 January 2016|date=9 May 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715074045/http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10265~3816628,00.html|archivedate=15 July 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2003/settembre/21/Pagliuca_numero_viaggia_500_co_0_030921119.shtml|title=Pagliuca, il numero 1 viaggia in 500|language=italian|date=21 September 2003|author=Vincenzo Di Schiavi|newspaper=[[Corriere della Sera]]|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref> Throughout his career, he played for [[UC Sampdoria|Sampdoria]], [[Internazionale Milano F.C.|Inter]], Bologna, and [[Ascoli Picchio F.C. 1898|Ascoli]] in Italy, winning several domestic and international trophies.<ref name=yahoo>{{cite web|url=https://it.sports.yahoo.com/calcio/gianluca-pagliuca.html |title=Gianluca Pagliuca |website=[[Yahoo Sports]] |language=italian |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927194117/https://it.sports.yahoo.com/calcio/gianluca-pagliuca.html |archivedate=27 September 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> At international level, he represented Italy at three FIFA World Cups (1990, 1994, and [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]]), most notably reaching the [[1994 FIFA World Cup Final|1994 World Cup final]] as Italy's starting goalkeeper.\n\nHe is the [[Football records in Italy#Appearances|fifth highest capped player]] (592 caps), and the [[Football records in Italy#Most penalties saved|best penalty-stopper]] (24 saves) in [[Serie A]],<ref name=penalties/> although other specialists such as [[J\u00falio C\u00e9sar (football goalkeeper, born 1979)|J\u00falio C\u00e9sar]] and [[Samir Handanovi\u0107]] have a higher success rate.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2012/aprile/25/Handa_Julio_intreccio_lungo_metri_ga_10_120425024.shtml|title=Handa-Julio, intreccio lungo 11 metri|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=italian|date=25 April 2012|accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\nPagliuca was born in Bologna. In his club career, he played for Sampdoria (1987\u201394), Internazionale (1994\u201399), Bologna (1999\u20132006), and Ascoli (2006\u201307). His most notable successes with Sampdoria include one [[Cup Winners' Cup]] and one ''Scudetto''; he also reached a [[UEFA Champions League]] [[1992 European Cup Final|final]], losing 1\u20130 to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in [[1991\u201392 European Cup|1992]], at [[Wembley Stadium (1923)|Wembley]], in spite of his impressive performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1992/maggio/21/Samp_cade_passo_dalla_storia_co_0_92052115122.shtml|title=La Samp cade a un passo dalla storia|author=Giancarlo Padovan|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|date=21 May 1992|p=42|accessdate=16 January 2016|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nIn 1994, he moved from Sampdoria to Internazionale from a then world record fee for a goalkeeper of \u00a37 million. With the ''nerazzurri'' he reached two consecutive [[UEFA Cup]] finals, losing the first one against [[Schalke 04]] in [[1996\u201397 UEFA Cup|1997]] and winning the second one in [[1997\u201398 UEFA Cup|1998]], when he captained the side to a 3\u20130 win over [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]. Pagliuca left Inter in 1999, moving to his home town club, Bologna, after the former Juventus boss [[Marcello Lippi]] took charge of Inter and signed [[Angelo Peruzzi]] from his former club.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/maggio/27/Inter_Pagliuca_divorzio_con_scintille_co_0_9905275439.shtml?refresh_ce-cp|title=Inter-Pagliuca, un divorzio con scintille|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|author=Giancarla Ghisi|p=43|date=27 May 1999|accessdate=16 January 2016|language=Italian}}</ref><ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\">{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/1999/luglio/10/Peruzzi_para_cattiverie_ga_0_9907103110.shtml|title=Peruzzi para le cattiverie|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Nicola Cecere|date=10 July 1999|accessdate=29 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nAfter Bologna were relegated to [[Serie B 2005\u201306|Serie B]] in [[2004\u201305 Serie A|2004\u201305]], despite Pagliuca's outstanding season,<ref name=guerin>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/italpoy.html#guerin|title=Guerin d'Oro - List of winners|website=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=16 January 2016}}</ref> he stayed with the club for one more year; then he returned to Serie A, accepting a contract with Ascoli for one year starting in summer of [[Serie A 2006\u201307|2006]]. On 17 September 2006, Pagliuca set the record for most Serie A appearances for a goalkeeper, overtaking [[Dino Zoff]], as he started against [[F.C. Messina Peloro|Messina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/5354172.stm |title=Pagliuca sets new Serie A record |publisher=BBC SPORT, Football, Europe |date=17 September 2006 |accessdate=26 November 2015 }}</ref> He retired at the end of the season.\n\n==International career==\nAfter taking part in the [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990 World Cup]] without playing a minute, Pagliuca overtook [[Walter Zenga]], [[Stefano Tacconi]] and [[Luca Marchegiani]], becoming first choice goalkeeper for Italy at the [[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994 World Cup]] under Arrigo Sacchi. He received the dubious honour of being the first goalkeeper to be [[Ejection (sports)#Association football|sent off]] in a World Cup match, when he was dismissed for handling outside his area against [[Norway national football team|Norway]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.yahoo.com/italys-pagliuca-becomes-first-keeper-see-red-225303185.html|title=Italy's Pagliuca becomes first keeper to see red|newspaper=[[Yahoo! News]]|author1=Pan Pylas|author2=Anne-Marie Belgrave|date=6 June 2014|accessdate=19 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305163220/https://news.yahoo.com/italys-pagliuca-becomes-first-keeper-see-red-225303185.html|archivedate=5 March 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> However, he returned after suspension to feature from the quarter-finals onwards with his team losing to [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] in a penalty shootout. Despite the loss, Pagliuca became the first ever goalkeeper to save a penalty from a shootout in a World Cup final, denying [[Marcio Roberto dos Santos|Marcio Santos]] his shot.<ref>{{cite news|author=Giancarlo Padovan|author2=Luca Valdiserri|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1994/luglio/18/Baggio_sbaglia_tiro_della_sua_co_0_9407181835.shtml|title=E Baggio sbaglia il tiro della sua vita|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|p=3|date=18 July 1994|accessdate=8 July 2015|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nIn 1995, Pagliuca's international career was halted by the emergence of [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] goalkeeper [[Angelo Peruzzi]], his perceived career rival,<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\"/> and it would be two years before he returned to the Italy senior squad, although he took part at the [[Football at the Summer Olympics|Olympics]] with the [[Italy national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] as an overage player in [[Football at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|1996]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/mensolympic/atlanta1996/teams/team=1889316/index.html|title=Olympic Football Tournaments Atlanta 1996 - Men|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=14 January 2018}}</ref> Under [[Cesare Maldini]], Pagliuca would have taken part to the [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998 World Cup]] only as a back-up, but he earned the starting spot because of a last-minute injury to Peruzzi.<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\"/> He made one of the saves of the tournament, again against Norway, when he shot out a hand to prevent [[Tore Andr\u00e9 Flo]]'s point-blank header from netting.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1998/giugno/29/Pagliuca_pronto_parare_Francia_co_0_98062912758.shtml|title=Pagliuca \u00e8 pronto a parare la Francia|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|author=Fabio Monti|p=39|date=29 June 1998|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref> However, Italy lost against host country [[France national football team|France]] in the quarter-final after the [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]], even though Pagliuca blocked [[Bixente Lizarazu]]'s shot.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.repubblica.it/online/sport/itafra/itafra/itafra.html|title=L'Italia \u00e8 fuori, ancora ai rigori|newspaper=la Repubblica|date=3 July 1998|accessdate=8 July 2015|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nAfter the tournament, the emergence of fellow keepers [[Francesco Toldo]] and [[Gianluigi Buffon]] (who were, themselves, Pagliuca's deputies in the 1998 World Cup), along with Peruzzi's recovery from his injury, put an end to Pagliuca's international career on 39 caps.<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\"/>\n\n==Style of play==\nAn agile, consistent and athletic goalkeeper,<ref name=corriere1>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1995/settembre/01/Del_Piero_Pagliuca_puniti_Casa_co_0_9509015710.shtml|title=Del Piero Pagliuca, i puniti di Casa Italia|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|author1=Giancarlo Padovan|author2=Roberto Perrone|language=italian|date=1 September 1995|accessdate=15 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=corriere2>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1995/giugno/05/Vialli_Rambo_Tarzan_Pagliuca_ecco_co_0_95060511464.shtml|title=Vialli Rambo, Tarzan Pagliuca: ecco la nazionale della Forza|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|author=Giorgio Rondelli|language=Italian|date=5 June 1995|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref> Pagliuca was renowned for his excellent reactions,<ref name=corriere1/><ref name=corriere2/> diving saves,<ref name=\"sfida con Zenga\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,33/articleid,0696_01_1995_0056_0041_10284761/|title=Peruzzi. La mia sfida con Zenga|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|language=Italian|date=26 February 1995|author=Marco Ansaldo|p=33}}</ref> and penalty-stopping abilities,<ref name=penalties>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2008/ottobre/25/Rigori_riparte_sfida_degli_Infallibili_co_9_081025099.shtml|title=Rigori, riparte la sfida degli infallibili|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|author=Paolo Tomaselli|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref> as well as his control of the ball, accurate distribution, and deep goal kicks with his left foot.<ref name=corriere1/><ref name=corriere2/><ref name=treccani>{{cite web|url=http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/gianluca-pagliuca_%28Enciclopedia_dello_Sport%29/|publisher=[[Enciclopedia Treccani]]|title=PAGLIUCA, Gianluca|author=Fabio Monti|date=2002|accessdate=7 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=ilnumero1>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilnumero1.it/intervista-a-luca-marchegiani-giocare-con-i-piedi-che-trauma/|title=Intervista a Luca Marchegiani: \"Giocare con i piedi, che trauma!\"|publisher=Il Numero 1|language=Italian|date=4 January 2014|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2001/marzo/14/Buffon_Van_der_Sar_maestri_ga_0_0103144255.shtml|title=Buffon e Van der Sar maestri con i piedi|trans-title=Buffon and Van der Sar masters with their feet|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author=Matteo Dore|date=14 March 2001|accessdate=23 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"diversi\">{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,34/articleid,0777_01_1993_0065_0058_10977320/|title=Tacconi: cos\u00ec bravi, cos\u00ec diversi|publisher=La Stampa|accessdate=30 October 2017|page=34|language=Italian|author1=Bruno Bernardi|date=7 March 1993}}</ref> In addition to being very gifted acrobatics-wise, he also possessed a good positional sense.<ref name=\"Sarti vota Marchegiani\">{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,33/articleid,0696_01_1995_0056_0041_10284763/|title=Sarti vota Marchegiani|publisher=La Stampa|page=41|language=Italian|date=26 February 1995|accessdate=1 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2005/03/08/un-solo-segreto-averne-voglia-tutti-santi.html|title=Un solo segreto averne voglia tutti i santi giorni|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|date=8 March 2005|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref> Although he was capable of coming off the line to handle crosses, he performed better between the posts.<ref name=sfida>{{cite news|title=Pagliuca e Zenga, sfida all'ultimo volo|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,27/articleid,0881_01_1991_0225_0027_12268576/|p=27|date=22 September 1991|accessdate=10 July 2016}}</ref> Nicknamed ''The Wall'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/memories-gianluca-pagliuca-semplicemente-the-wall/|title=Memories: Gianluca Pagliuca, semplicemente \"the Wall\"|publisher=U.C. Sampdoria|date=29 January 2010|accessdate=10 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archivio.panorama.it/archivio/Ho-imparato-a-parare-di-tutto-palloni-e-delusioni|title=Ho imparato a parare di tutto: palloni e delusioni|newspaper=Panorama|author=Giancarlo Dotto|accessdate=10 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712005843/http://archivio.panorama.it/archivio/Ho-imparato-a-parare-di-tutto-palloni-e-delusioni|archive-date=12 July 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> due to his goalkeeping abilities and consistency,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1993/02/26/un-anima-comune.html|title=UN' ANIMA COMUNE|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=GIANNI MURA|date=26 February 1993|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref> he also distinguished himself by his strong temper,<ref name=sfida/><ref name=sogni>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/1997/aprile/16/Pagliuca_sogni_dietro_porta_ga_0_9704164112.shtml|title=Pagliuca, i sogni dietro la porta|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|language=Italian|date=16 April 1997|author1=Nicola Cecere|author2=Franco Arturi|accessdate=30 December 2016}}</ref> which occasionally had a negative impact on his performances, when he let his emotions get the better of him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.corriere.it/speciali/2004/Sport/campionato/perrone/perrone12.shtml|title=Richiami dal passato: non perdete la bussola|publisher=Il Corriere della Sera|language=Italian|author1=ROBERTO PERRONE|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1995/09/28/il-mio-settembre-nero.html|title=' IL MIO SETTEMBRE NERO'|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=GIANNI PIVA|date=28 September 1995|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/05/13/processo-zenga-leader-perduto.html|title=PROCESSO A ZENGA LEADER PERDUTO|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=GIANNI PIVA|date=13 May 1994|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1994/02/23/altra-samp-serve-la-difesa.html|title=L' ALTRA SAMP: SERVE LA DIFESA|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=STEFANO ZAINO|date=23 February 1994|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Pagelle\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,31/articleid,0679_01_1995_0275_0029_9185951/|title=Le pagelle di Tacconi|trans-title=Tacconi's report cards|publisher=[[La Stampa]]|author1=Stefano Tacconi|language=Italian|page=29|date=10 October 1995|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nUnder coaches [[Sven-G\u00f6ran Eriksson]] and [[Arrigo Sacchi]], who relied on high defensive lines, Pagliuca used to play as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)#Sweeper-keeper|sweeper-keeper]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/giugno/28/portieri_anche_piedi_hanno_ali_co_0_93062814308.shtml|title=Portieri, anche i piedi hanno le ali|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|language=italian|date=28 June 1993|accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archivio.lastampa.it/articolo?id=2126c5b12e9ac92942dc00277c5fad39a941c8d1|title=Pagliuca-show, Roma sempre pi\u00f9 gi\u00f9|language=italian|newspaper=La Stampa|date=18 January 1993|accessdate=15 October 2015}}</ref> Known for his dedication, physical conditioning, and work-rate, Pagliuca also stood out for his ability to avoid injury and longevity throughout his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/aprile/11/Pagliuca_mette_malattia_ga_0_9904112932.shtml|title=Pagliuca si mette in malattia|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Nicola Cecere|author2=Luca Curino|author3=Raffaele Mignano|date=11 April 1999|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2005/03/08/pagliuca-il-tramonto-puo-attendere.html|title=Pagliuca, il tramonto pu\u00f2 attendere|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=VALENTINA DESALVO|date=8 March 2005|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//2005/settembre/03/Uno_tutti_sw_0_0509031892.shtml |title=Uno su tutti |publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport |language=Italian |author1=Iacopo Iandiorio |date=3 September 2005 |accessdate=30 May 2018 }}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|Leagu